    "narrative": "The Austin Waves head into today\u2019s slate with a potent offensive outlook, anchored by three elite plays with scores eclipsing the 70-point threshold. **Kyle Tucker** (77.10) leads the charge despite a 35% rain risk in his matchup against Landen Roupp; his combination of high-end xwOBA, favorable wind conditions, and a batting order advantage makes him our highest-ceiling option. Close behind is **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (74.92), who benefits from a plush matchup against Jack Kochanowicz and a strong 5.35 xERA opposing starter, providing a premier floor for our utility spot. Meanwhile, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (74.56) remains a must-start at 2B; his dynamic platoon advantage against RHP and the favorable 6.36 xERA of the opposing starter project him as a major contributor to our daily efficiency goals.\n\nStrategic focus on stolen base potential remains the primary engine of our lineup construction. **Jackson Merrill** (70.77) earns his spot with a significant park-adjusted boost, while **Nasim Nunez** (68.23) continues to offer high efficiency against weak pitching despite his lower-tier lineup slot. Conversely, the most difficult decision of the day involved **Marcell Ozuna**, who sat just outside the starting nine with a score of 53.80. While **Ozuna** represents a solid professional hitter, the optimizer favored **Andy Pages** (62.83) due to his superior situational alignment and the wind-aided boost at his park, despite the latter's minor risk concerning catcher pop time. \n\nWe are monitoring several moving parts heading into first pitch. **Gunnar Henderson** (57.76) and **Kyle Tucker** are our most significant \"Lineup Pending\" risks, and both face external volatility\u2014**Henderson** battles a tough Kris Bubic platoon split, while **Tucker** faces that persistent 35% rain threat. Additionally, while **Luis Robert Jr.** (52.42) remains in the lineup, his score is suppressed by the matchup against an elite-holding pitcher, emphasizing 